  <revision rev="12" vrev="1">
    <srcmd5>c48846c439053ddd99dbc29ff37c1d54</srcmd5>
    <version>2.0.14</version>
    <time>1782377881</time>
    <user>anag_factory</user>
    <comment>Update to 2.0.14. Adds clpeak-install-bindir.patch (install binary into bindir via GNUInstallDirs; upstream PR krrishnarraj/clpeak#178). Drops _service and builds straight from the upstream release tarball.</comment>
    <requestid>1361626</requestid>
  </revision>
  <revision rev="13" vrev="1">
    <srcmd5>bfa9ba5a346299d8cadf2bbee42112d7</srcmd5>
    <version>2.0.16</version>
    <time>1782576385</time>
    <user>dimstar_suse</user>
    <comment>Update to clpeak 2.0.16: the downstream bindir-install fix is now upstream (PR #178), LICENSE installed via CMake, C++14 build fix, and new CUDA GPU support (Blackwell Ultra/GB10/Jetson Thor). Drops clpeak-install-bindir.patch.</comment>
    <requestid>1361855</requestid>
  </revision>
  <revision rev="14" vrev="1">
    <srcmd5>fb10830eb007d406c4f5a6b9c8bc3264</srcmd5>
    <version>2.0.17</version>
    <time>1783525037</time>
    <user>anag_factory</user>
    <comment>Update to 2.0.17: clamp work-group size to per-kernel device max; fix DCE-inflated throughput in CUDA WMMA/MMA and Metal simdgroup_matrix benchmarks; native mma.sync tensor-core path with full-rate FP16; joint_matrix on Intel Arc A770.</comment>
    <requestid>1364433</requestid>
  </revision>
  <revision rev="15" vrev="1">
    <srcmd5>b9c00bcf77db23d4a1edbbc286ed31d4</srcmd5>
    <version>2.0.18</version>
    <time>1783945668</time>
    <user>dimstar_suse</user>
    <comment>- Update to 2.0.18:
  * Major expansion of the native CPU backend with new benchmark probes for
    recent x86 and ARM ISA extensions (AVX-VNNI / AVX10.2 / AMX, SVE/SVE2,
    AES/SHA crypto, string and UTF-8 validation kernels)</comment>
    <requestid>1365244</requestid>
  </revision>
